      "duration": "PT4M5S",
      "description": "Lisa (2013) is a hybrid artwork by Alexandre Mury that unfolds across videoperformance, video art, performative self-portraiture, photography, body art and critical fiction. Conceived through the living archive of Leonardo da Vinci's Mona Lisa / La Gioconda, the work activates the portrait as a field of temporal, corporeal and hermeneutic transformation. Through shaving, depilation, vertical video, art-historical memory, music, voice and self-representation, Lisa operates as a hybrid dramaturgy and as an auto-implicative gesture that interrogates the survival of inherited images, the instability of identity, gender performativity and the corporeal dimension of interpretation.",
